The migration from `InMemoryEventBus` to an external message broker with the Transactional Outbox pattern addresses critical scalability and resilience limitations in the UtilityChain Core Suite. While introducing operational complexity, the benefits—particularly guaranteed delivery, temporal decoupling, and horizontal scalability—are essential for mainnet readiness with high transaction volumes and complex DeFi protocols.

