## 5. Resilience and Error Handling Strategy

### 5.1 New Failure Modes Introduced

| Failure Mode | Description | Mitigation |
|--------------|-------------|------------|
| **Network Partition** | Node loses connectivity to broker | Circuit breaker + local buffering |
| **Broker Downtime** | RabbitMQ cluster unavailable | Outbox pattern ensures eventual delivery |
| **Poison Messages** | Messages that repeatedly fail processing | Dead Letter Queue + manual intervention |
| **Consumer Lag** | Subscribers can't keep up with producers | Backpressure, scaling consumers |
| **Message Expiry** | TTL exceeded before processing | Alerting, DLQ inspection |
| **Duplicate Delivery** | At-least-once semantics can cause duplicates | Idempotent handlers (deduplication) |

### 5.2 Dead Letter Queue (DLQ) Strategy

